Class UniversalType

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.construct.UniversalConstruct<TypeMirror, UniversalType>
org.microbean.construct.type.UniversalType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Constable, AnnotatedConstruct, ArrayType, DeclaredType, ErrorType, ExecutableType, IntersectionType, NoType, NullType, PrimitiveType, ReferenceType, TypeMirror, TypeVariable, UnionType, WildcardType
public final class UniversalType extends UniversalConstruct<TypeMirror, UniversalType> implements ArrayType, ErrorType, ExecutableType, IntersectionType, NoType, NullType, PrimitiveType, TypeVariable, UnionType, WildcardType
A TypeMirror and UniversalConstruct implementation.
Author:
Laird Nelson

    • UniversalType

      public UniversalType(TypeMirror delegate, PrimordialDomain domain)
      Creates a new UniversalType.
      Parameters:
      delegate - a TypeMirror to which operations will be delegated; must not be null
      domain - a PrimordialDomain from which the supplied delegate is presumed to have originated; must not be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if either argument is null
      See Also:
      • UniversalConstruct.delegate()

    • UniversalType

      public UniversalType(TypeMirror delegate, List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotations, PrimordialDomain domain)
      Creates a new UniversalType.
      Parameters:
      delegate - a TypeMirror to which operations will be delegated; must not be null
      annotations - a List of AnnotationMirror instances representing annotations, often synthetic, that this UniversalType should bear; may be null in which case only the annotations from the supplied delegate will be used
      domain - a PrimordialDomain from which the supplied delegate is presumed to have originated; must not be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if any argument is null
      See Also:
      • UniversalConstruct.delegate()

    • prototypical

      public final boolean prototypical()
      Returns true if and only if this UniversalType represents a prototypical type.

      Prototypical types are not defined by the Java Language Specification. They are partially defined by the specification of the TypeElement#asType() method.

      Returns:
      true if and only if this UniversalType represents a prototypical type

    • of

      public static final UniversalType of(TypeMirror t, PrimordialDomain domain)
      Returns a non-null UniversalType that is either the supplied TypeMirror (if it itself is null or is a UniversalType) or one that wraps it.
      Parameters:
      t - a TypeMirror; may be null in which case null will be returned
      domain - a PrimordialDomain; must not be null
      Returns:
      a UniversalType, or null (if t is null)
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if domain is null
